    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-02-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-02-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="451"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d451">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.003/271</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Acting Secretary of State</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-02-06">February 6,
                            1930</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Japanese Ambassador came in today and left the attached note.<note n="61"
                        xml:id="d451fn61">
                        <hi rend="italic">Infra.</hi>
                    </note> He states this is a statement without reservation of the Japanese
                    position as to extraterritoriality and he invites a similar statement of the
                    American position if we can give it to him. I told him I would answer him.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>J[<hi rend="smallcaps">oseph</hi>] P. C[<hi rend="smallcaps"
                        >otton</hi>]</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
